European Settlement __________________________________________________________________
In this unit students examine causes, issues, and events surrounding European settlement in the Americas during the seventeenth and eighteenth centuries.
They explain how Europeans adapted to life in North America and examine colonial policy toward Native Americans and African slaves.
They do this by using primary sources to construct accounts of past events.
They also explore cultural conflicts between the European settlers and other groups.
To culminate the unit, students compose an essay explaining the effects of colonization.
